  "prompt": "Do Kit Kat bars have peanut ingredients?",
  "response": "Kit Kat bars, in their standard form, do not typically contain peanuts as an ingredient. However, it is important to note that manufacturing processes can vary, and there may be a risk of cross-contamination with peanuts or other nuts in facilities that process multiple products. \n\nIf you have a peanut allergy, it's crucial to check the packaging for any allergen warnings or contact the manufacturer directly for the most accurate and updated information. Kit Kat offers a variety of flavors and special editions, some of which might include nuts, so always review the specific product packaging for ingredient details.",
